   NASA Educational Links
   spacer
   The National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA) has been
   providing educational materials for educators and their students for
   many years.
   To date, the primary on-line resources for educators have been:

   NASA Education Program offers a rich slate of enrichment and study
   opportunities for students and educators, ranging from grade school to
   post-doctorate levels.

   Spacelink is NASA's Electronic Library of Educational Resources. Here
   you will find a wealth of knowledge about Space Science. They have a
   powerful search engine at this site that can help you track down
   anything relating to NASA.

   Quest at Ames Research Center is NASA's K-12 Internet Initiative. This
   is a highly interactive site that features chats with scientists, video
   feeds to the Space Shuttle and much more.

   NASA Centers are the 10 Field Research Centers that are scattered
   throughout the United States. Each Center has a specific mission. The
   centers sponsor the projects that NASA supports. Each project has an
   education and outreach component.

